C.  Rural  Water  Supply  and  Sanitation  Specialist  (international,  4  person-months, 
intermittent) 
7.  The rural water supply and sanitation specialist (intermittently over 12 months) will be a 
senior expert in rural water supply and sanitation, including experience in sector policy dialogue 
and development, community-based water and sanitation, social development, identification and 
preparation of loan and TA projects, and capacity development, with a minimum of 15 years' 
experience. The consultant, who will report to the team leader, should have experience in the Asia 
and Pacific region, preferably in Indonesia, and possess a good command of Bahasa Indonesia.

